<br>
I really think that melee classes deserve something similar to the spellcasting focus effects. Something like a &quot;skill focus&quot; that would offer a bonus to a skill or stat or other ability.<br>
<br>
E.g. Bracers of Crushing:<br>
AC12 Str +3 <br>
Skill Focus: Crushing Damage +1<br>
<br>
Basically, this would make any blunt / crushing weapon have the equivalent of +1 to the damage/delay ratio. So, just like with focus spell effects, the skill foci would be dependant on using the right weapons or abilities.<br>
<br>
I think it would be nice to see the following:<br>
Crushing Damage<br>
Crushing Speed<br>
Slashing Damage<br>
Slashing Speed<br>
Piercing Damage<br>
Piercing Speed<br>
<br>
Basically these would all either affect the damage of the particular weapon type by a number, or reduce the delay of the weapon type. I think the speed might be a tad powerful so it might be limited to a single level (e.g. you might get a skill focus of Crushing Damage +3, but you could never get Crushing Speed +3)<br>
<br>
Some other things I think might be good:<br>
Improved Taunt, Improved Bash, Improved Kick - would all reduce the time to re-use these abilities.<br>
<br>
So what do you think? I don't think coming out with new weapons is necessarily the right way to go. New disciplines might be good, but I think having the option to specialize in something would be better than having the *same* discipline that every other warrior, paladin or shadowknight might have. <br>
<br>
Note I also haven't played a high-season melee class so I'm just going on what I've heard from others, and what I've seen from my short time playing a halfling warrior (to 33rd season)<br>
<br>
Ideas? Wish lists? Comments? Let's hear 'em<br>
