<br>
I think in many cases it would be applied to items that are already in the game. For instance, when focus effects were first introduced, overnight my golden efreeti boots became MUCH better. I still wear my golden efreeti boots, and the focus effect that was added (Enhancement Haste) is soooo nice and convenient.<br>
<br>
I think it would be good, perhaps for a way to make certain items more attractive that otherwise wouldn't get used. <br>
<br>
These items might be expensive, but I think many of the better focus effect items are just as expensive. Polished Mithril Masks seem pretty darn expensive, and I have yet to see an affordable Improved Healing III or Improved Healing IV on the market... although I must admit I don't spend a lot of time looking when my bank balance is perpetually under 1.5k<br>
