<br>
It's called +str, +sta, +agi, etc...  See, melee stats help a melee hit harder and take more abuse.  Before focus effects however, casters could have all the gear in the world, but their level 9 spells still does the exact same damage it did at level 9.  Focus effects is gear for casters like normal stat gear is for melee. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bjond>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2492<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/15/03 6:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1557.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   You gotta be kidding me</span><hr size=1> It's already hellishly difficult to balance hp/ac/resists in the end game and now you want to add a fourth variable to the whole gear balancing scenario?  Perhaps undo or invalidate hundreds of hours of work on a character's gear when you consider end-game gear and that nearly all that gear on all servers is no-drop?  Yuck.<br>
<br>
